comments.en: This is a platform build for ontologies used in planning trips

comment.en: The timetable for a transportation service, defining when it operates and at what times it reaches various stops or stations
An organization that provides transportation services, such as a railway company, bus operator, or airline
A journey from one location to another, consisting of one or more segments using various modes of transportation. A trip has a defined start point, end point, and follows an itinerary.
A single portion of a trip using one specific mode of transportation between two locations. Multiple trip segments form a complete itinerary
An individual who travels or uses transportation services. A person can be associated with bookings and trips
The method of transportation used for a trip segment, such as train, bus, car, or walking
A  area relevant to trip planning, such as a departure area, destination, or intermediate stop. Locations can be residential addresses, transportation hubs, or destination.
A defined path between locations that is followed by a transportation service. Routes consist of a sequence of stops or waypoints.
A complete plan of a trip, consisting of ordered trip segments that together form the journey from the origin to the destination.
A reservation for a specific transportation service, accommodation, or other travel-related service for a particular date and time.
A specific service provided by a transportation company, such as a train line, bus route, or flight route
